===Etymology===
* From the [[Greek]] [[συριακός]] ''(syriakós)'', an adjective pertaning to [[Συρία]] ''(Syría)'', the Greek name for [[Aram]], and probably based on the name [[Assyria]].

===Proper noun===
'''Syriac''' (''plural:'' Syriacs)
# An [[Aramaic]] language, part of the [[Semitic]] [[language group]], specifically:
#* The language of the kingdom of [[Osrhoene]].
#* The [[liturgical]] language of various [[church]]es with roots in the [[Middle East]].
# A person who either speaks Syriac or is a member of the Syriac Orthodox Church, or both.

====Related terms====
*[[Syria]], [[Syrian]], [[Assyrian]], [[Assyria]], [[Aramaic]], [[Aramaean]].

===Adjective===
'''Syriac'''
# Referring to the Syriac language, for example, Syriac [[alphabet]], Syriac [[culture]], Syriac [[poetry]].

